  meanings
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "The decision or judgement of a jury or court; a verdict."
          example "The court returned a sentence of guilt in the first charge, but innocence in the second."
        entry
          definition "The judicial order for a punishment to be imposed on a person convicted of a crime."
          example "The judge declared a sentence of death by hanging for the infamous cattle rustler."
        entry
          definition "A punishment imposed on a person convicted of a crime."
        entry
          definition "A saying, especially from a great person; a maxim, an apophthegm."
        entry
          definition "(grammar) A grammatically complete series of words consisting of a subject and predicate, even if one or the other is implied, and typically beginning with a capital letter and ending with a full stop."
          example "The children were made to construct sentences consisting of nouns and verbs from the list on the chalkboard."
        entry
          definition "A formula with no free variables."
        entry
          definition "Any of the set of strings that can be generated by a given formal grammar."
        entry
          definition "Sense; meaning; significance."
        entry
          definition "One's opinion; manner of thinking."
        entry
          definition "A pronounced opinion or judgment on a given question."
      partOfSpeech noun
      synonyms (conviction verdict)
    entry
      definitions
        entry
          definition "To declare a sentence on a convicted person; to doom; to condemn to punishment."
          example "The judge sentenced the embezzler to ten years in prison, along with a hefty fine."
        entry
          definition "To decree or announce as a sentence."
        entry
          definition "To utter sententiously."
      partOfSpeech verb
  phonetic "[ˈsɛntn̩t͡s]"
